      "id": 1,
      "text": "Dumont was incorporated as the Borough of Schraalenburgh on July 20, 1894, carved from Harrington and Palisades Townships.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        29
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://grokipedia.com/page/Dumont%2C_New_Jersey"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "In 1898 the borough was renamed Dumont after its first mayor, Dumont Clarke, shifting from Dutch to anglicized name.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        6
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://grokipedia.com/page/Dumont%2C_New_Jersey"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "The New Jersey and New York Railroad station opened in 1873, sparking residential and commercial growth in southern Dumont.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        2
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://grokipedia.com/page/Dumont%2C_New_Jersey"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "The Derick Banta House, a surviving historic site, shows local militia support during the Revolutionary War.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
